Create “ Blood Alcohol” Chart 16

Step 1:  Creating a chart based on the previous Chart (Time Chart).

1.     Copy and paste " Time” Chart. Use Ctrl V to paste the chart.

2.     Delete the "Month, Year, Day, Holiday " From the shared axis 

3.     Drag and drop "Blood Alcohol " column to the shared axis 

Step 2: Configure the “Blood Alcohol” chart

         Click on the Format icon on the visualization bar

a.    General Tab

·         X- Position: 0

·         Y Position:  430

·         Width: 506

·         Height: 290

·         Legend: ON

·         Position: Top

·         Title: OFF

 

b.    Configure the X axis: ON

·         Keep the same format from the previous Chart (Time Chart). 

c.    Configure the Y- axis

 

1.    Y-axis Column

·         Position: Left

·         Scale type: Liner

·         Start: - 20

·         End: Auto

·         Keep the same format for the rest from the previous (time chart)

2.    Y- axis Line

·         Position: Right

·         Start: - 0.2

·         End: Auto

·         Keep the same format the rest.

3.    Keep the same Format for Data Color, Data Label, Shape, Background and Boarder, Change only the title to “Blood Alcohol”


Follow the gif below to format the “Blood Alcohol” Chart
